&lt;li&gt;Participate in the selection and evaluation of Vendors, ensuring that they meet quality standards and regulatory requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and approve GCP/GVP-related documentation, including study protocols, study reports, and other relevant documents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that documentation is accurate, complete, and compliant with regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate/participate in Quality Oversight Committee meetings with Vendors and develop and maintain quality agreements with Vendors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 10 or more years of experience in FDA regulated industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous hands-on experience with Veeva Quality Docs, Veeva Training, and Veeva QMS req

