&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Kailera, we are bold, authentic and committed to our mission of developing therapies that give people the power to transform their lives and elevate their overall health. Rooted in an entrepreneurial spirit and a team-oriented culture, we are working together to advance Kailera’s mission to advance novel therapies for obesity and related conditions. &lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;We are passionate about creating an inclusive workplace that promotes collaboration, integrity, and excellence. As we expand, we seek the most talented individuals with diverse backgrounds, cultures, perspectives, and experiences to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Vice President, Public Policy is responsible for leading Kailera&#39;s public policy strategy and analysis, providing executive leadership with insights into the legislative, regulatory, reimbursement and healthcare policy developments that influence the company&#39;s business and long-term growth strategy. Reporting to the Chief Corporate Affairs Officer, this leader will serve as the company&#39;s internal expert on healthcare policy, translating complex policy issues into actionable business recommendations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will work cross-functionally with Market Access, Regulatory Affairs, Medical Affairs, Clinical Development, Commercial, Legal, Investor Relations, and Communications to assess the implications of evolving healthcare policies across the product lifecycle. The Vice President will help shape the company&#39;s policy positions, support enterprise decision-making, and ensure Kailera is prepared to navigate an increasingly dynamic policy environment as it advances a differentiated obesity portfolio.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Required location: Waltham, MA (hub-based, onsite 3-4 days per week)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the company&#39;s analysis of federal, state, and international healthcare policy developments that may impact Kailera&#39;s business, pipeline and commercial strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and evaluate legislative and regulatory proposals affecting obesity treatment, pharmaceutical innovation, reimbursement, pricing, market access, and healthcare delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze evolving reimbursement policies across Medicare, Medicaid, and commercial payers, identifying implications for patient access, coverage, and long-term business strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the company&#39;s subject matter expert on healthcare policy issues, including drug pricing reform, the Inflation Reduction Act, Most Favored Nation (MFN) pricing proposals, government pricing programs, international reference pricing, tariff policies, and other emerging policy initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor FDA and broader regulatory policy developments affecting obesity therapies, including clinical development, manufacturing, compounded medicines, telehealth prescribing, and evolving regulatory frameworks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop strategic analyses, policy scenarios, and risk assessments to support enterprise planning and executive decision-making&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare policy briefings, presentations, and recommendations for the Executive Leadership Team and Board of Directors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Market Access to anticipate reimbursement trends and evaluate policy changes that could influence commercialization strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Regulatory Affairs, Medical Affairs, Clinical Development, Commercial, and Legal to ensure policy considerations are incorporated into business planning&lt;/li&gt;
